    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Christiern Winther [?] to Miklós Oláh (Leuven, 24 March
                    1535)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>Oláh is toiling every day to make sure he supports as many people as
                            possible; he has people within his household who want to reciprocate
                            Oláh’s good deeds with their diligence and tirelessness. It is no wonder
                            that the Queen entrusts her secrets to such an excellent person, the
                            dignity of whose mind is solid and unflinching. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Christiernus Umbra Cymber<note type="critic">Probably Christiern
                        Winther, see <hi rend="smallcap">Tournoy</hi> 2015, 527; and <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Christiansen</hi> 2002, 82.</note> Nicolao Olao suo
                    salutem.</p>
                <p>Quamquam praeclari ingenii tui dexteritas mira quadam morum maturitate
                    unita, tum aetas, quae et ipsa iam quoque maturuit, palam arguunt et perspicue,
                    te viri consummati, ita circulum absolvisse, ut nulla aut vix ulla iam amplius
                    quaeat fieri accessio, nihilominus adeo otium non amplecteris, quin
                    honestissimis studiis intentus, contendas quotidie te ipsum, si fieri possit,
                    superare, tanquam <persName>Neoptolemus</persName><note type="critic">He was
                        Achilles’ son.</note> quispiam Martis et militiae ignarus, arma manibus
                    diurnis nocturnisque vigilans versare solet, ne rudis in harena cum hoste <choice>
                        <orig>congredietur</orig>
                        <supplied>congrediatur</supplied>
                    </choice> turpiter succubiturus. Quae res vel hoc argumento abunde claret, Vir
                    virtute Ornatissime, quod intra parietes domesticos a latere habeas ac foveas,
                    qui quaeunt sua vigilantia atque industria, tuas dotes alioqui ditissimas
                    ditiores reddere, pro quorum salute exacto anno, ut audio, non parum sollicitus
                    sudasti, quo nomine ex professo famulum me tibi invenias devinctiorem. Tum usus
                    et litteratorum necessitudo accedit, quam huic negotio impense conferre, vel
                        <quote>talpae appareat.</quote><note type="quote">Cf. Erasm. <hi
                            rend="italic">Adag</hi>. 255. I, III, 55. Talpa caecior; and 3571. IV,
                        VI, 71. Loquax talpa.</note> In primis <persName>Cornelii
                        Sceperi</persName>,<note type="critic">Cornelis de Schepper.</note> viri et
                    singularis prudentiae et doctrinae undevis exquisitissimae, qui haud dubie
                    divino ingenio donatus, tum facundiae flumine <milestone unit="pb"/>iuxta
                    praeditus, omnium de se opinione aut est superior, aut genius parum propitius,
                    nobis tenebras ob oculos offuderit, unde indicitum caliginem contraxerit. Ad hoc
                    mare felicitatis, tamquam quaedam auctaria, adfluunt felicissimae dotes, quas in
                    ista generosa <choice>
                        <orig>monte</orig>
                        <supplied>mente</supplied>
                    </choice> deprehendi, quae ulla oblivione e mea memoria non poterunt facile
                    intercipi. Nempe candor, ingenii canities, humanitas, venustas, gravitas, quae
                    te heroi affinem facit, quibus omnibus veluti anteambulonibus et pedissequis
                    quibusdam uteris familiariter, ut minime mirum sit, si princeps illustrissima
                    talem sibi delegerit, ac sua arcana concredierit sapientissime. Huiusmodi
                    viatica, patria viduata ab hostibus, tecum hospes absportas, quem quamvis
                    hostilis tyrannus violenta manu bonorum fortuitorum bona parte dispoliarit, tuae
                    tamen mentis sublimitas eis fortunae fluctibus manet semper inconcussa atque
                    immersabilis, nec unquam labascit, aut victa infringitur nihilomagis,
                        <quote>quam Marpesia cautes,</quote><note type="quote">Verg. <hi
                            rend="italic">Aen</hi>. VI,471.</note> undis undique insultantibus
                    quassa commovetur. </p>
                <quote>
                    <lg>
                        <l>Has tu reliquias retines a caede tuorum,</l>
                        <l>quas non saeva manus, non mille hostilia tela</l>
                        <l>Turcarumve cohors adimit tibi, turba cruenta,</l>
                        <l>nec fortuna potens, potis est auferre beatus</l>
                        <l>quo minus eis ducibus divos confisus adibis</l>
                        <l>famaque post fatum non interitura manebis.</l>
                    </lg>
                </quote>
                <note type="quote">It is probably a poem by Winther, but it has not been
                    confirmed.</note>
                <p>Vale, Nicolae Generosissime, nec credas Colacem<note type="critic"
                        >Colax was the title of pieces written by Ennius and Plautus. The name means
                        ‘flatterer’.</note> quempiam adulari, ut ventri prospectum sit. Nam <choice>
                        <orig>ταῦτην τῆν</orig>
                        <supplied>ταύτην τὴν</supplied>
                    </choice> γραφὴν σου<note type="critic">‘this writing of yours’.</note> a viris
                    multo emunctissimae naris accepi. Dominum <persName>Cornelium
                        Sceperum</persName>, quo cum per otium etiam litteris nugabor, ex me saluta
                    et nostra nugamenta boni consule. Iterum vale. </p>
                <p><placeName>Lovanii</placeName> ex aedibus <persName>Rutgeri
                        Rescii</persName><note type="critic">Rutger Ressen.</note> XXIIII. Martii
                    anno MDXXXV.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
